1
00:00:06,842 --> 00:00:10,080
A servant like you has nothing to lose!

2
00:00:10,100 --> 00:00:12,240
My love has dignity too.

3
00:00:14,094 --> 00:00:17,280
Focus on your study and forget everything.

4
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:19,341
[11 Years Later]

5
00:00:22,702 --> 00:00:24,480
This is Captain Phobthee Munkongphak,

6
00:00:24,755 --> 00:00:26,520
a representative from army's Artillery Division.

7
00:00:26,632 --> 00:00:27,880
Nice to meet you,

8
00:00:29,267 --> 00:00:30,280
Prince Tinnakorn.

9
00:00:36,102 --> 00:00:37,696
Why didn't you stay to watch the show?

10
00:00:37,904 --> 00:00:40,120
It isn't because of the show reminded you of our past, is it?

11
00:00:40,208 --> 00:00:41,339
That's why you can't stand watching it.

12
00:00:41,382 --> 00:00:43,400
I told you that I forget all about it.

13
00:02:36,667 --> 00:02:37,668
Oh, hey.

14
00:02:43,611 --> 00:02:44,920
Do you want to try it?

15
00:02:47,579 --> 00:02:51,059
I don't think so, I don't want to break your camera.

16
00:02:52,910 --> 00:02:54,899
You're so great.

17
00:02:55,267 --> 00:02:57,539
You can write and you can take photos.

18
00:02:58,379 --> 00:03:00,139
I want to be good at something like you.

19
00:03:01,859 --> 00:03:04,899
Oh dear, why do you want to be like me?

20
00:03:05,539 --> 00:03:07,379
I should be the one who's jealous of you.

21
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:10,659
You have everything; the look, the noble title

22
00:03:11,339 --> 00:03:13,939
and your perfect date like Prince Tinnakorn.

23
00:03:20,299 --> 00:03:21,819
Is everything okay?

24
00:03:28,702 --> 00:03:30,601
Hi, Siri.

25
00:03:31,209 --> 00:03:32,210
There you are.

26
00:03:32,899 --> 00:03:34,939
I got caught up at work so I was late to the show.

27
00:03:35,854 --> 00:03:37,819
Well, who is this?

28
00:03:39,299 --> 00:03:42,459
Chat, this is Ms. Janthorn.

29
00:03:42,629 --> 00:03:44,630
She's a journalist from Lok Siam newspaper.

30
00:03:44,787 --> 00:03:47,019
A journalist from Lok…Siam?

31
00:03:49,099 --> 00:03:50,303
It's you!

32
00:03:50,725 --> 00:03:52,899
You've constantly dragged my name through the mud in your paper!

33
00:03:55,321 --> 00:03:57,179
Give it to me! Give it to me now.

34
00:03:57,289 --> 00:03:58,719
- It's mine.
- Let it go.

35
00:03:58,910 --> 00:04:01,179
- Give it to me.
- It's mine.

36
00:04:01,267 --> 00:04:02,499
- Let it go.
- Give it back to me.

37
00:04:02,568 --> 00:04:04,931
- Let it go and give it to me.
- It's mine.

38
00:04:05,043 --> 00:04:08,339
- Janthorn?
- Did you take a photo of me? Give it to me.

39
00:04:08,404 --> 00:04:09,939
- Give it to me.
- It's mine.

40
00:04:10,033 --> 00:04:12,699
Let me see, what photos did you take?

41
00:04:12,801 --> 00:04:14,299
What are you doing?

42
00:04:14,481 --> 00:04:18,299
Didn't you know that she's a journalist from Lok Siam newspaper?

43
00:04:20,478 --> 00:04:22,201
They attacked the government

44
00:04:22,457 --> 00:04:23,939
and royal family members like us.

45
00:04:24,494 --> 00:04:27,219
I'm writing only facts, I didn't attack anyone.

46
00:04:27,678 --> 00:04:30,019
What facts? You're such a smart mouth.

47
00:04:31,439 --> 00:04:33,059
You're jealous at someone like us.

48
00:04:36,609 --> 00:04:37,610
Give it to me!

49
00:04:38,667 --> 00:04:40,299
Judging from your action,

50
00:04:40,819 --> 00:04:42,219
I think you deserved all those bad words about you.

51
00:04:43,299 --> 00:04:46,019
You bullied a woman in broad daylight.

52
00:04:46,465 --> 00:04:47,466
Phob!

53
00:04:49,254 --> 00:04:52,179
You're taking her side?

54
00:04:54,919 --> 00:04:57,939
You lowlife scumbags!

55
00:04:58,899 --> 00:05:00,259
People like you

56
00:05:00,331 --> 00:05:02,379
have never done anything to benefit the nation!

57
00:05:03,859 --> 00:05:05,589
You're useless!

58
00:05:07,531 --> 00:05:08,859
You're speaking as if

59
00:05:09,899 --> 00:05:11,900
you own a nation.

60
00:05:13,379 --> 00:05:16,339
This land is not reserved only for royal family members.

61
00:05:17,217 --> 00:05:18,619
It belongs to everyone

62
00:05:18,961 --> 00:05:20,699
who gave their blood and sweats to the nation,

63
00:05:22,199 --> 00:05:23,659
including servants

64
00:05:24,300 --> 00:05:25,301
like us.

65
00:05:27,257 --> 00:05:30,179
Noble people who take advantage of

66
00:05:30,382 --> 00:05:33,383
and tyrannize people in lower status deserve to be called useless.

67
00:05:33,459 --> 00:05:35,379
- Phob!
- Chat, let go.

68
00:05:36,296 --> 00:05:38,139
People are watching you.

69
00:05:38,230 --> 00:05:40,019
You're not ashamed of that?

70
00:05:53,099 --> 00:05:54,259
Are you alright?

71
00:06:07,809 --> 00:06:10,089
I'm sorry about my brother's behavior.

72
00:06:11,083 --> 00:06:13,619
If there is anything broken, please let me know.

73
00:06:13,918 --> 00:06:15,299
I'm happy to be responsible for that.

74
00:06:15,982 --> 00:06:17,419
Nothing is damaged.

75
00:06:18,905 --> 00:06:22,219
You're nothing like your brother.

76
00:06:25,641 --> 00:06:27,739
How are you going back home?

77
00:06:28,622 --> 00:06:30,009
Can I give you a ride?

78
00:06:30,115 --> 00:06:33,379
So you can see the doctor and check if you're hurt.

79
00:06:33,819 --> 00:06:34,820
It's okay.

80
00:06:35,278 --> 00:06:36,926
Phob can give me a ride.

81
00:06:37,182 --> 00:06:38,819
I'll stop at his place for dinner first.

82
00:06:43,619 --> 00:06:46,659
How long have you two been close friends?

83
00:06:47,254 --> 00:06:49,931
We've been friends since

84
00:06:50,001 --> 00:06:52,219
Phob left Varakulvatin Palace for a while.

85
00:06:52,625 --> 00:06:54,859
Phob and his mom lived in Ayutthaya

86
00:06:55,126 --> 00:06:57,379
but one of the noblemen scammed their rental.

87
00:06:57,403 --> 00:06:58,839
His hand got slashed so bad.

88
00:07:02,579 --> 00:07:03,580
Where is my money?

89
00:07:03,742 --> 00:07:05,179
It's not time to pay yet.

90
00:07:09,339 --> 00:07:12,099
Oh my goodness!

91
00:07:12,838 --> 00:07:15,057
No! Don't break my things!

92
00:07:15,185 --> 00:07:17,179
Don't break them! Oh my!

93
00:07:20,547 --> 00:07:22,483
Stop! Don't hurt my son.

94
00:07:23,021 --> 00:07:24,779
- Phob, are you okay?
- Mom!

95
00:07:26,969 --> 00:07:28,379
- Phob!
- Where's the money?

96
00:07:28,465 --> 00:07:31,039
I'll get you the money, don't hurt my son.

97
00:07:33,118 --> 00:07:35,659
Here, take it all. You can have it all.

98
00:07:35,705 --> 00:07:37,706
Don't hurt my son! Please!

99
00:07:38,366 --> 00:07:39,659
That's it.

100
00:07:40,819 --> 00:07:41,820
Let's go.

101
00:07:45,297 --> 00:07:46,298
Phob!

102
00:07:46,459 --> 00:07:47,819
How are you?

103
00:07:56,761 --> 00:07:58,739
- His hand got slashed?
- That's right.

104
00:08:03,499 --> 00:08:04,719
When he filed a complaint,

105
00:08:04,937 --> 00:08:07,738
they falsely accused him and he almost went to jail.

106
00:08:08,074 --> 00:08:10,299
Auntie Nual struggled so hard to helpher son

107
00:08:10,457 --> 00:08:12,659
and her valuables were all sold.

108
00:08:13,038 --> 00:08:15,299
That's why they moved to Bangkapi

109
00:08:15,339 --> 00:08:16,939
and met me.

110
00:08:20,147 --> 00:08:21,939
He was struggled that bad?

111
00:08:22,779 --> 00:08:25,940
Yes. Good for him that he is an excellent student.

112
00:08:26,118 --> 00:08:29,139
So he pass the test to be a soldier and won a scholarship to France.

113
00:08:34,659 --> 00:08:37,859
I heard from Princess Ruethaisiri that when he lived in the palace,

114
00:08:38,267 --> 00:08:40,339
you two were close, right?

115
00:08:41,979 --> 00:08:44,980
I guess we both are his best friends.

116
00:08:45,780 --> 00:08:46,819
I don't think so.

117
00:08:48,398 --> 00:08:51,419
You were with him when he had a hard time in life.

118
00:08:53,219 --> 00:08:55,739
Instead, I was the one who gave him the hard time.

119
00:09:08,694 --> 00:09:09,695
So tasty.

120
00:09:11,019 --> 00:09:12,020
Everything is so good.

121
00:09:14,475 --> 00:09:15,476
Let me help you.

122
00:09:19,478 --> 00:09:22,099
Your cooking skill has never changed, still so good.

123
00:09:23,206 --> 00:09:25,059
You're such a sweet talker, always.

124
00:09:25,779 --> 00:09:29,019
I should cook a beef spicy salad for you.

125
00:09:29,619 --> 00:09:31,259
Please? Thank you.

126
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:38,480
Now you're talking nicely.

127
00:09:46,969 --> 00:09:49,419
You look so tense, what is on your mind?

128
00:09:50,409 --> 00:09:52,099
Are you thinking about Prince Tinnakorn?

129
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:57,301
Nonsense.

130
00:09:58,115 --> 00:09:59,259
Why would I be thinking about him?

131
00:10:02,859 --> 00:10:04,499
I can tell

132
00:10:04,786 --> 00:10:07,239
that you two were close once.

133
00:10:08,179 --> 00:10:10,099
He is a conservative

134
00:10:10,380 --> 00:10:12,299
and we are progressives.

135
00:10:12,939 --> 00:10:16,139
You two were friends who stand on the different sides,

136
00:10:16,740 --> 00:10:18,341
it must be so awkward.

137
00:10:20,502 --> 00:10:22,459
You can't go soft on him.

138
00:10:22,870 --> 00:10:24,939
We still need insight info from Prince Tinnakorn.

139
00:10:25,339 --> 00:10:26,340
Do you understand?

140
00:10:28,699 --> 00:10:29,700
I know.

141
00:10:30,649 --> 00:10:32,299
I will go to see him tomorrow

142
00:10:32,979 --> 00:10:34,499
and I will get it done.

143
00:10:36,585 --> 00:10:37,586
Hey!

144
00:10:39,499 --> 00:10:41,459
You went to see Prince Tinnakorn?

145
00:10:57,550 --> 00:10:58,551
Phob.

146
00:10:59,929 --> 00:11:01,779
Why do you need to see him again?

147
00:11:04,379 --> 00:11:06,619
Mom, I told you. It's just for work.

148
00:11:08,059 --> 00:11:11,260
The military needs to help him with the Phra Nakhon's celebration.

149
00:11:15,579 --> 00:11:16,739
Are you sure about that?

150
00:11:23,649 --> 00:11:24,659
Don't you worry.

151
00:11:25,761 --> 00:11:26,819
Prince Tinnakorn

152
00:11:28,819 --> 00:11:30,139
will be engaged to Princess Ruethaisiri.

153
00:11:33,235 --> 00:11:34,236
He forgets about me,

154
00:11:35,439 --> 00:11:36,819
all about me.

155
00:11:39,279 --> 00:11:40,659
There is no bonding left between us.

156
00:11:43,299 --> 00:11:44,300
What about you?

157
00:11:46,379 --> 00:11:47,579
Did you forget about him?

158
00:11:56,147 --> 00:11:57,148
Phob.

159
00:11:58,619 --> 00:12:00,739
You need to forget

160
00:12:02,579 --> 00:12:03,899
what hurt you.

161
00:12:06,269 --> 00:12:07,279
Your wish

162
00:12:08,299 --> 00:12:10,039
can never come true.

163
00:12:12,606 --> 00:12:15,019
The sky is high and the ground is low.

164
00:12:16,659 --> 00:12:20,339
We are living in a different world than he is.

165
00:12:33,169 --> 00:12:35,179
It doesn't have to always be like that.

166
00:12:41,803 --> 00:12:42,979
What do you mean?

167
00:13:10,202 --> 00:13:11,203
Chat?

168
00:13:11,865 --> 00:13:13,867
About the soldiers' reimbursement that Phob asked you,

169
00:13:13,990 --> 00:13:15,059
you took care of it, right?

170
00:13:15,659 --> 00:13:17,190
It's all done, Dad.

171
00:13:17,613 --> 00:13:18,614
Good.

172
00:13:19,025 --> 00:13:20,499
Don't embarrass me again.

173
00:13:35,059 --> 00:13:36,339
Janthorn's article

174
00:13:37,219 --> 00:13:39,459
encouraged people to speak up what they used to be afraid of.

175
00:13:41,187 --> 00:13:42,588
The wind is on our side.

176
00:13:45,819 --> 00:13:48,539
We need to start our mission on the celebration day as our original plan.

177
00:13:49,579 --> 00:13:50,739
We can't make a mistake.

178
00:13:52,099 --> 00:13:55,100
We need to know the schedule of all royal family members, in every detail.

179
00:13:55,739 --> 00:13:57,939
We need to know what places they will visit,

180
00:13:58,185 --> 00:14:00,940
when they will visit and who will be around them.

181
00:14:02,619 --> 00:14:05,059
If you want a schedule, then it is easy.

182
00:14:05,459 --> 00:14:06,860
Like we discussed earlier,

183
00:14:07,299 --> 00:14:09,200
Phob was close to Prince Tinnakorn.

184
00:14:09,539 --> 00:14:10,865
He grew up in the palace.

185
00:14:14,540 --> 00:14:16,499
It's time for Siam's transition.

186
00:14:18,399 --> 00:14:20,179
You're our hope.

187
00:14:31,070 --> 00:14:32,071
Yes, sir.

188
00:14:41,659 --> 00:14:43,118
[M.C. Tinnakorn Varakulvatin - His Majesty's Principal Private Secretary]

189
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:44,441
What?

190
00:14:45,039 --> 00:14:48,040
You're asking for the royal family member's schedule on the celebration day?

191
00:14:49,579 --> 00:14:50,980
Why is it related to your job?

192
00:14:51,654 --> 00:14:52,699
I need to know

193
00:14:53,265 --> 00:14:55,339
so I can provide protection to all of them.

194
00:14:56,169 --> 00:14:57,170
Provide protection?

195
00:14:58,419 --> 00:14:59,420
From who?

196
00:15:03,025 --> 00:15:03,826
Do you believe that

197
00:15:03,889 --> 00:15:06,459
someone would be dissatisfied and they would start to protest?

198
00:15:06,758 --> 00:15:07,979
It is possible.

199
00:15:08,499 --> 00:15:09,939
People are in distress

200
00:15:10,449 --> 00:15:11,553
people are stuggling to live.

201
00:15:12,171 --> 00:15:13,439
In the meantime, some noble people

202
00:15:13,739 --> 00:15:16,839
focus on organizing fancy parties and neglect those who are beneath them.

203
00:15:17,171 --> 00:15:18,979
This is considered as take advantage of

204
00:15:19,094 --> 00:15:20,269
people living in lower status.

205
00:15:20,295 --> 00:15:22,019
All of us are not the same.

206
00:15:23,787 --> 00:15:25,788
You ived in Varakulvatin Palace,

207
00:15:26,419 --> 00:15:28,139
- and it gave you life.
- That's right.

208
00:15:29,979 --> 00:15:31,139
I remember it so well.

209
00:15:32,259 --> 00:15:33,460
The place gave me life

210
00:15:35,073 --> 00:15:36,389
but it took something from me.

211
00:15:39,139 --> 00:15:40,259
It got destroyed to pieces.

212
00:15:45,553 --> 00:15:46,554
Where are you going?

213
00:15:47,425 --> 00:15:49,139
Why are you trying to avoid this subject?

214
00:15:53,936 --> 00:15:54,937
What's wrong?

215
00:15:56,299 --> 00:15:57,779
We used to be even closer than this.

216
00:15:59,030 --> 00:16:00,779
Are you sure you want to forget all about it?

217
00:16:03,259 --> 00:16:04,260
That's right.

218
00:16:05,339 --> 00:16:06,539
I don't remember a thing.

219
00:16:18,275 --> 00:16:19,276
Your past

220
00:16:19,939 --> 00:16:21,219
could mean nothing to you.

221
00:16:22,139 --> 00:16:23,140
That's right.

222
00:16:24,640 --> 00:16:26,179
You should forget about it too.

223
00:16:27,541 --> 00:16:28,602
It meant nothing.

224
00:16:29,379 --> 00:16:31,259
If you forget all about it,

225
00:16:32,299 --> 00:16:33,820
do you want me to remind you?

226
00:16:37,139 --> 00:16:38,140
Let me go.

227
00:16:42,640 --> 00:16:43,899
If you want me to let you go,

228
00:16:46,097 --> 00:16:47,819
your voice needs to be stronger than this.

229
00:17:28,449 --> 00:17:29,779
This one is pretty.

230
00:17:30,081 --> 00:17:32,699
I know, right? I think so, too.

231
00:17:33,019 --> 00:17:34,539
I like this bright blue.

232
00:17:35,499 --> 00:17:37,500
Thank you so much

233
00:17:37,588 --> 00:17:40,689
for accompanying me to pick our the fabric.

234
00:17:40,699 --> 00:17:42,939
We are just two old ladies,

235
00:17:43,046 --> 00:17:47,179
where we are going and what we pick out

236
00:17:47,342 --> 00:17:48,659
are so outdated.

237
00:17:50,639 --> 00:17:52,379
Who are you calling 'old ladies'?

238
00:17:52,839 --> 00:17:56,019
I'm still young and fresh.

239
00:17:56,267 --> 00:17:58,177
I can walk smoothly.

240
00:17:58,239 --> 00:18:00,979
I can get up and sit back down easily.

241
00:18:01,859 --> 00:18:04,339
I will get you! I will get you good.

242
00:18:04,439 --> 00:18:06,099
Stop with your funny comments already.

243
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:09,219
We're not at our palace, okay?

244
00:18:12,691 --> 00:18:15,019
I need to look over there.

245
00:18:15,278 --> 00:18:17,659
- Where is it?
- They're so pretty.

246
00:18:20,681 --> 00:18:22,282
- Aum.
- Yes, ma'am?

247
00:18:23,779 --> 00:18:27,139
Phob and Tin

248
00:18:27,457 --> 00:18:29,019
were so close when they were young.

249
00:18:30,331 --> 00:18:33,779
Why did Phob leave the palace?

250
00:18:34,406 --> 00:18:37,539
It's because of Phob's mom,

251
00:18:37,713 --> 00:18:40,339
I mean…Captain Phobthee,

252
00:18:40,843 --> 00:18:43,499
resigned to sell her products out of the city.

253
00:18:43,787 --> 00:18:46,179
Then we lost touch with her.

254
00:18:47,259 --> 00:18:49,339
They were so close

255
00:18:50,379 --> 00:18:51,380
why did they

256
00:18:52,794 --> 00:18:53,795
lose touch all of a sudden?

257
00:18:54,419 --> 00:18:55,939
Good question, ma'am.

258
00:18:56,420 --> 00:18:58,779
Right, in the middle of one night,

259
00:18:58,985 --> 00:19:01,986
Phob sneaked into the palace to meet Prince Tinnakorn.

260
00:19:02,526 --> 00:19:06,127
But his father forbade

261
00:19:06,179 --> 00:19:08,459
all of us to talk about Phob the next morning.

262
00:19:08,980 --> 00:19:12,699
Before Prince Tinnakorn left to study in the UK,

263
00:19:13,419 --> 00:19:15,179
he asked me to bring Phob

264
00:19:15,459 --> 00:19:17,979
a letter when he was in Ayutthaya.

265
00:19:19,810 --> 00:19:21,139
What letter?

266
00:19:22,359 --> 00:19:24,539
I can't read so I wouldn't know.

267
00:19:24,571 --> 00:19:27,979
If I can read, I'd read the letter already.

268
00:19:29,275 --> 00:19:30,419
I was just kidding.

269
00:19:32,709 --> 00:19:34,339
Why did you ask?

270
00:19:36,702 --> 00:19:38,219
If you forget all about it,

271
00:19:39,619 --> 00:19:40,859
do you want me to remind you?

272
00:19:42,799 --> 00:19:43,800
Let me go.

273
00:19:45,165 --> 00:19:46,339
If you want me to let you go,

274
00:19:46,894 --> 00:19:48,699
your voice needs to be stronger than this.

275
00:20:07,395 --> 00:20:09,099
I baked some breads

276
00:20:09,611 --> 00:20:11,459
but I was too clumsy, I dropped them.

277
00:20:15,219 --> 00:20:16,220
Hi, Phob.

278
00:20:17,478 --> 00:20:18,479
I didn't know you were coming.

279
00:20:28,639 --> 00:20:31,939
I just feel like they're not so close anymore.

280
00:20:32,003 --> 00:20:33,004
That's why I'm asking.

281
00:20:35,758 --> 00:20:37,259
Oh my goodness, my princess.

282
00:20:38,059 --> 00:20:39,299
Excuse me, ma'am.

283
00:20:58,025 --> 00:20:59,054
People are stuggling to live.

284
00:20:59,102 --> 00:21:00,379
In the meantime, some noble people

285
00:21:00,686 --> 00:21:03,779
focus on organizing fancy parties and neglect those who are beneath them.

286
00:21:04,062 --> 00:21:05,819
This is considered as take advantage of

287
00:21:05,982 --> 00:21:07,259
people living in lower status.

288
00:21:42,505 --> 00:21:43,506
Your Highness,

289
00:22:14,897 --> 00:22:16,259
you are still the same.

290
00:22:17,499 --> 00:22:19,979
You're a lightweight and you still like to drink.

291
00:22:22,059 --> 00:22:23,939
I'm not a good drinker like you are.

292
00:22:24,931 --> 00:22:26,499
You can drink all night and you feel nothing.

293
00:22:31,579 --> 00:22:32,580
I'm sorry.

294
00:22:38,694 --> 00:22:40,139
Why are you apologizing to me?

295
00:22:43,265 --> 00:22:45,699
Janthorn told me that after you left the palace,

296
00:22:45,739 --> 00:22:47,189
you and your mom had to struggle to live.

297
00:22:48,326 --> 00:22:50,739
A nobleman scammed your rental,

298
00:22:50,779 --> 00:22:52,411
you lost everything and almost went to jail.

299
00:22:56,161 --> 00:22:58,179
Is that why you hate us so much?

300
00:23:00,278 --> 00:23:01,279
That's right.

301
00:23:02,731 --> 00:23:03,979
We struggled to live.

302
00:23:06,379 --> 00:23:07,859
But the most painful experience

303
00:23:10,189 --> 00:23:11,590
wasn't the fact that I almost went to jail,

304
00:23:12,950 --> 00:23:14,739
or lost everything,

305
00:23:18,166 --> 00:23:19,619
it was that letter.

306
00:23:22,167 --> 00:23:23,168
Phob?

307
00:23:24,950 --> 00:23:26,219
Every letter

308
00:23:27,299 --> 00:23:28,539
on paper

309
00:23:30,161 --> 00:23:31,739
was so cruel and it cut me deep.

310
00:23:34,347 --> 00:23:35,899
I wanted to burn the letter.

311
00:23:37,867 --> 00:23:38,939
But I couldn't

312
00:23:41,868 --> 00:23:43,219
because it was the last thing

313
00:23:44,259 --> 00:23:45,660
that you gave me.

314
00:23:49,499 --> 00:23:51,259
It reminded me of

315
00:23:52,702 --> 00:23:54,059
how stupid I used to be.

316
00:23:57,499 --> 00:23:59,819
I'm sorry for causing you pain.

317
00:24:02,819 --> 00:24:03,820
But I..

318
00:24:04,410 --> 00:24:07,839
I still meant every word I said in the letter.

319
00:24:08,579 --> 00:24:11,699
Both of us should forget everything.

320
00:24:15,639 --> 00:24:16,739
I can forget it.

321
00:24:18,870 --> 00:24:20,779
But you need to prove to me

322
00:24:22,899 --> 00:24:24,539
that you forget all about it as well.

323
00:24:27,259 --> 00:24:28,260
Prove how?

324
00:25:55,363 --> 00:25:56,899
Are you back, sir?

325
00:26:01,499 --> 00:26:02,500
Oh my!

326
00:26:03,059 --> 00:26:05,060
What bit you?

327
00:26:05,419 --> 00:26:07,839
Look at that, your neck is red.

328
00:26:08,929 --> 00:26:09,930
A mosquito.

329
00:26:11,099 --> 00:26:12,100
Just a mosquito.

330
00:26:13,579 --> 00:26:14,580
A mosquito.

331
00:26:17,501 --> 00:26:20,299
You poor thing, it must be so painful.

332
00:27:07,931 --> 00:27:10,219
Phob and his mom lived in Ayutthaya

333
00:27:10,359 --> 00:27:12,659
but one of the noblemen scammed their rental.

334
00:27:12,685 --> 00:27:14,189
His hand got slashed so bad.

335
00:27:14,349 --> 00:27:15,659
When he filed a complaint,

336
00:27:15,779 --> 00:27:18,539
they falsely accused him and he almost went to jail.

337
00:27:19,039 --> 00:27:21,179
Auntie Nual struggled so hard to helpher son

338
00:27:21,355 --> 00:27:23,499
and her valuables were all sold.

339
00:27:24,171 --> 00:27:27,139
You were with him when he had a hard time in life.

340
00:27:29,009 --> 00:27:31,499
Instead, I was the one who gave him the hard time.

341
00:27:43,345 --> 00:27:45,179
Your Highness? Sir?

342
00:28:54,278 --> 00:28:57,019
There is an update from the group asking for the regime change?

343
00:28:58,190 --> 00:29:01,819
I heard that many parties are involved,

344
00:29:02,014 --> 00:29:03,489
including the military,

345
00:29:04,039 --> 00:29:07,640
law graduates, civil officials,

346
00:29:07,649 --> 00:29:08,839
and journalists.

347
00:29:09,795 --> 00:29:12,979
The coordinator is a soldier from Artillery Division,

348
00:29:13,094 --> 00:29:14,499
he is close to Kitti.

349
00:29:20,342 --> 00:29:21,659
I am Captain Phobtheee

350
00:29:22,499 --> 00:29:23,899
from Artillery Division.

351
00:29:24,700 --> 00:29:26,701
I am representing the division and I'm here to ask for clarity

352
00:29:27,179 --> 00:29:29,499
about pension payment for junior rank soldiers.

353
00:29:33,219 --> 00:29:34,659
I don't care who they are,

354
00:29:35,579 --> 00:29:39,099
if they wish to overthrow the regime, they will face with death penalty.

355
00:29:47,622 --> 00:29:48,899
- Aum?
- Yes, sir?

356
00:29:49,979 --> 00:29:50,980
Has Tin left for work yet?

357
00:29:51,209 --> 00:29:53,419
I haven't seen him.

358
00:29:54,078 --> 00:29:55,259
Is everything okay?

359
00:30:24,955 --> 00:30:26,539
Your Highness! Your Highness!

360
00:30:28,799 --> 00:30:29,800
Your Highness!

361
00:30:33,534 --> 00:30:34,535
Let's go.

362
00:30:35,614 --> 00:30:36,615
Your Highness!

363
00:30:38,099 --> 00:30:39,100
Your Highness!

364
00:31:01,809 --> 00:31:02,810
Tin!

365
00:31:04,097 --> 00:31:05,239
What's going on? What?

366
00:31:05,779 --> 00:31:09,139
I saw you and Phob last night, on Charoenkrung Road.

367
00:31:14,280 --> 00:31:15,281
What?

368
00:31:15,839 --> 00:31:16,840
What did you see?

369
00:31:20,841 --> 00:31:22,579
I saw you get out of Phob's car.

370
00:31:22,921 --> 00:31:24,019
What did you do in his car?

371
00:31:27,422 --> 00:31:28,659
I met him by chance.

372
00:31:30,279 --> 00:31:31,339
What is it?

373
00:31:32,070 --> 00:31:33,639
You two met by chance?

374
00:31:34,139 --> 00:31:35,219
Why did you get in his car?

375
00:31:36,539 --> 00:31:38,039
There was nothing.

376
00:31:38,465 --> 00:31:39,639
We need to work together.

377
00:31:43,259 --> 00:31:44,299
Listen to me.

378
00:31:45,899 --> 00:31:47,739
He is a bad person.

379
00:31:49,179 --> 00:31:50,859
He didn't mean well to us.

380
00:31:51,379 --> 00:31:53,419
He didn't care about Dad, he didn't care about me.

381
00:31:55,721 --> 00:31:58,099
He was a servant who happened to do great in his career.

382
00:31:58,139 --> 00:31:59,539
That's why he is arrogant.

383
00:32:00,339 --> 00:32:03,619
Therefore, you can't be around him, you hear me?

384
00:32:03,849 --> 00:32:05,699
He will ruin your reputation,

385
00:32:05,739 --> 00:32:07,139
and our family's reputation.

386
00:32:07,189 --> 00:32:10,190
The only person who is ruining the family's reputation is you.

387
00:32:11,439 --> 00:32:12,639
You should worry more about yourself.

388
00:32:13,139 --> 00:32:14,139
Don't worry about me.

389
00:32:14,739 --> 00:32:16,239
I was just worried about you.

390
00:32:22,803 --> 00:32:24,579
I'm worried that he could hurt you.

391
00:32:30,022 --> 00:32:31,139
In your eyes,

392
00:32:32,079 --> 00:32:33,499
I must be a really bad brother, right?

393
00:32:34,639 --> 00:32:35,640
No! Hey!

394
00:32:57,561 --> 00:32:59,139
You have a date with Tinnakorn, right?

395
00:33:00,595 --> 00:33:01,596
That's right.

396
00:33:03,299 --> 00:33:04,539
Dad?

397
00:33:05,547 --> 00:33:07,839
What if I didn't want to marry Tin?

398
00:33:10,107 --> 00:33:11,139
Why wouldn't you?

399
00:33:11,585 --> 00:33:12,939
His dad and I had an agreement.

400
00:33:14,670 --> 00:33:16,539
What if he didn't love me?

401
00:33:17,294 --> 00:33:19,259
It doesn't matter if he loves you or not.

402
00:33:20,099 --> 00:33:22,939
Our family needs to be bonded with Varakulvatin.

403
00:33:23,689 --> 00:33:26,819
You're a woman, you will have to marry and have children.

404
00:33:27,214 --> 00:33:28,779
Why did you think about it too much?

405
00:33:30,139 --> 00:33:31,679
I have a friend.

406
00:33:32,387 --> 00:33:35,819
She's a talented woman, she can do so many things.

407
00:33:36,162 --> 00:33:38,899
She can make a living independently.

408
00:33:39,643 --> 00:33:40,779
That's absurd.

409
00:33:41,543 --> 00:33:43,819
She is a commoner.

410
00:33:43,889 --> 00:33:45,339
Of course, she needs to work hard to make a living.

411
00:33:47,369 --> 00:33:48,699
You were born in a royal family.

412
00:33:50,014 --> 00:33:51,939
Your duty is to maintain your pride.

413
00:33:52,862 --> 00:33:54,663
You have to marry Tinnakorn.

414
00:34:10,079 --> 00:34:11,080
You?

415
00:34:26,430 --> 00:34:27,939
Hey! What are you doing?

416
00:34:32,883 --> 00:34:34,139
I missed you.

417
00:34:35,609 --> 00:34:36,819
Do you miss me?

418
00:34:37,742 --> 00:34:39,239
Stop doing something crazy.

419
00:34:40,859 --> 00:34:41,860
Something crazy?

420
00:34:43,019 --> 00:34:45,179
- But last night…
- I was drunk last night.

421
00:34:47,534 --> 00:34:48,535
You were drunk?

422
00:34:49,819 --> 00:34:50,820
That's right. I was drunk.

423
00:34:51,299 --> 00:34:52,300
Just drunk.

424
00:34:53,019 --> 00:34:55,259
I used to be drunk like this when I was a kid.

425
00:34:56,585 --> 00:34:57,739
You should know it well.

426
00:35:06,256 --> 00:35:07,419
We are not drunk right now,

427
00:35:08,859 --> 00:35:10,060
we should prove it

428
00:35:10,811 --> 00:35:12,239
to see if you really have no feeling for me.

429
00:36:07,456 --> 00:36:09,779
What? You said he just went in.

430
00:36:09,947 --> 00:36:11,299
Why is the door locked?

431
00:36:14,987 --> 00:36:16,699
Siri, I'm inside.

432
00:36:19,144 --> 00:36:20,145
I'll open the door for you.

433
00:36:30,781 --> 00:36:33,059
Hi, Phob. You're here, too?

434
00:36:38,419 --> 00:36:40,589
Siri, how are you doing?

435
00:37:00,285 --> 00:37:02,520
Hi, Phob. You're here, too?

436
00:37:08,899 --> 00:37:11,654
I hope that we will get another chance to discuss more about this.

437
00:37:11,846 --> 00:37:12,847
I'll see you later.

438
00:37:13,152 --> 00:37:14,153
Thank you.

439
00:37:24,713 --> 00:37:27,438
Hello? Are you here for a cup of coffee?

440
00:37:28,846 --> 00:37:30,059
Are you here by yourself?

441
00:37:32,102 --> 00:37:34,039
I was supposed to be here with Tinnakorn

442
00:37:35,214 --> 00:37:36,215
but..

443
00:37:37,879 --> 00:37:39,680
he's busy.

444
00:37:42,070 --> 00:37:43,071
If that so,

445
00:37:43,459 --> 00:37:47,039
can I join you instead of him?

446
00:37:47,704 --> 00:37:49,059
Sure, with my pleasure.

447
00:38:01,192 --> 00:38:03,499
Is something bothering you?

448
00:38:04,509 --> 00:38:05,839
You can tell me.

449
00:38:09,467 --> 00:38:11,899
It's about my friend.

450
00:38:13,099 --> 00:38:15,019
She has a fiancé.

451
00:38:15,600 --> 00:38:17,839
But it seems like her fiancé falls in love with someone else.

452
00:38:18,449 --> 00:38:20,139
We can punch his face.

453
00:38:20,523 --> 00:38:22,459
He's a player who hurts a woman's heart.

454
00:38:22,729 --> 00:38:24,899
We can't do that. Well…

455
00:38:25,291 --> 00:38:28,539
he is a really nice guy, but they're not in love.

456
00:38:29,379 --> 00:38:30,459
Also,

457
00:38:31,963 --> 00:38:34,789
my friend only see him as a brother,

458
00:38:34,819 --> 00:38:36,039
and nothing more.

459
00:38:37,339 --> 00:38:39,459
If they aren't in love to start with,

460
00:38:39,899 --> 00:38:42,139
why were they engaged?

461
00:38:43,162 --> 00:38:44,939
It's about suitability.

462
00:38:45,779 --> 00:38:47,539
Their parents took care of it.

463
00:38:49,780 --> 00:38:51,059
Arranged marriage couple?

464
00:38:53,001 --> 00:38:55,099
I think when two people are not in love,

465
00:38:55,459 --> 00:38:57,619
they won't be happy together.

466
00:38:58,041 --> 00:39:01,099
That is so easy. We can just…

467
00:39:01,419 --> 00:39:03,659
let him be with a person that he loves.

468
00:39:03,961 --> 00:39:05,589
She shouldn't try to keep him around.

469
00:39:07,702 --> 00:39:09,303
You're right about this.

470
00:39:11,534 --> 00:39:14,739
I feel so much better now that I talked to you.

471
00:39:15,999 --> 00:39:17,000
Well,

472
00:39:17,389 --> 00:39:21,339
can I buy you a cup of coffee as my way to thank you?

473
00:39:23,830 --> 00:39:24,831
Sure, thanks.

474
00:39:35,358 --> 00:39:36,359
Enjoy yourself.

475
00:39:40,019 --> 00:39:41,819
Hello, are you here by yourself?

476
00:39:43,672 --> 00:39:44,673
Welcome.

477
00:39:52,446 --> 00:39:54,659
Sir? How long have you been here?

478
00:39:55,803 --> 00:39:58,699
Right, Sakchai..

479
00:39:59,147 --> 00:40:01,539
- About the money…
- Oh, come on.

480
00:40:02,059 --> 00:40:04,379
We're friends, you can just pay me

481
00:40:04,739 --> 00:40:06,059
when you have enough money.

482
00:40:07,539 --> 00:40:08,689
Actually,

483
00:40:08,699 --> 00:40:11,700
I have something important to tell you.

484
00:40:12,859 --> 00:40:13,860
What is it?

485
00:40:17,118 --> 00:40:18,119
Well,

486
00:40:18,374 --> 00:40:21,179
I heard that a company owned by British people

487
00:40:21,384 --> 00:40:23,939
is looking for new investors

488
00:40:24,085 --> 00:40:26,039
to invest in mining business in Krabi.

489
00:40:28,006 --> 00:40:29,007
Really?

490
00:40:29,059 --> 00:40:30,260
Of course.

491
00:40:31,073 --> 00:40:33,459
I rushed here to tell you this.

492
00:40:33,590 --> 00:40:36,591
If you can invest in the company,

493
00:40:37,342 --> 00:40:39,039
I think we will be so rich.

494
00:40:40,179 --> 00:40:42,579
They will provide 30% of dividend yield

495
00:40:43,099 --> 00:40:44,459
per month, sir.

496
00:40:44,686 --> 00:40:45,739
That much?

497
00:40:48,043 --> 00:40:49,539
Think about it,

498
00:40:50,070 --> 00:40:52,579
if you become a major shareholder of this mine,

499
00:40:52,902 --> 00:40:56,379
you will be well-known and well-respected.

500
00:40:57,139 --> 00:40:59,939
You will bring great reputation to your family.

501
00:41:00,039 --> 00:41:01,859
Great reputation to the family.

502
00:41:03,299 --> 00:41:04,860
I don't have that much salary.

503
00:41:05,059 --> 00:41:07,973
- And I still to pay…
- About that…

504
00:41:08,060 --> 00:41:09,461
don't you worry.

505
00:41:09,819 --> 00:41:12,419
I have a plan for you.

506
00:41:15,391 --> 00:41:18,699
I heard that your ministry is about to do budget planning?

507
00:41:35,246 --> 00:41:37,739
Did you and Phob talk about something else besides work?

508
00:41:40,499 --> 00:41:42,019
Why did you want to know?

509
00:41:44,638 --> 00:41:45,979
My people suspected that

510
00:41:46,563 --> 00:41:49,739
Phob could be a part of the group wanting a regime change.

511
00:41:51,899 --> 00:41:52,900
Are you sure?

512
00:41:54,198 --> 00:41:55,680
There is no evidence.

513
00:41:57,758 --> 00:42:00,459
Did he say something suspicious?

514
00:42:04,441 --> 00:42:06,299
I'm not sure.

515
00:42:07,579 --> 00:42:08,939
We didn't talk much.

516
00:42:12,899 --> 00:42:14,859
Anyways, you have to be cautious.

517
00:42:16,099 --> 00:42:18,379
If he is acting suspiciously,

518
00:42:18,700 --> 00:42:19,701
you need to tell me.

519
00:42:21,499 --> 00:42:22,500
Yes, Dad.

520
00:42:31,496 --> 00:42:32,497
Forward, march.

521
00:42:48,640 --> 00:42:49,641
[Ministry of Defense]

522
00:42:50,520 --> 00:42:51,521
Your Highness.

523
00:42:55,515 --> 00:42:57,542
Are you here to watch the drill?

524
00:42:58,726 --> 00:43:00,000
The celebration day is right around the corner.

525
00:43:01,120 --> 00:43:02,976
I need to check for preparation,

526
00:43:03,840 --> 00:43:05,958
in case someone plans to stir something up.

527
00:43:11,088 --> 00:43:14,720
Your division showed great strength in marching,

528
00:43:15,360 --> 00:43:17,840
I guess Captain Phobthee should take credit for it.

529
00:43:20,240 --> 00:43:21,856
They should have been marching with better form.

530
00:43:23,174 --> 00:43:25,093
The soldiers look so exhausted,

531
00:43:25,995 --> 00:43:29,158
and it could be from delayed pension payment.

532
00:43:30,227 --> 00:43:31,560
It's just a little bit late.

533
00:43:31,955 --> 00:43:33,539
You shouldn't use it as an excuse.

534
00:43:35,139 --> 00:43:36,880
An economic recession happens across the world,

535
00:43:37,843 --> 00:43:39,720
even the noble people's salaries got cut.

536
00:43:40,760 --> 00:43:44,160
Their salaries got cut but they have their own assets

537
00:43:44,400 --> 00:43:45,880
to spend for the rest of their lives.

538
00:43:47,493 --> 00:43:49,099
For junior rank officials,

539
00:43:49,851 --> 00:43:51,720
it could be their death or alive situations.

540
00:43:52,496 --> 00:43:55,680
Many of them need to take care of many people.

541
00:43:56,742 --> 00:43:58,064
It'd be better

542
00:43:58,491 --> 00:44:01,320
if you care about your people.

543
00:44:04,443 --> 00:44:05,963
The noble people have money

544
00:44:06,166 --> 00:44:08,448
because they have been working hard for generations.

545
00:44:08,859 --> 00:44:10,800
We are not robbing anybody.

546
00:44:11,051 --> 00:44:12,640
It's true that you're not robbing anyone,

547
00:44:13,968 --> 00:44:15,440
but you can live like this

548
00:44:16,165 --> 00:44:18,480
because people in this country are working

549
00:44:19,547 --> 00:44:21,400
so hard to pay taxes.

550
00:44:23,262 --> 00:44:26,286
That's why Rattanakosin has been flourished for 150 years.

551
00:44:27,091 --> 00:44:28,696
It's true that people pay their taxes.

552
00:44:29,054 --> 00:44:31,300
Bur our Kings guided the nation

553
00:44:31,360 --> 00:44:33,280
and Siam has never been colonized by anybody.

554
00:44:34,144 --> 00:44:37,126
Also, Siam's honor can compete with other civilized nations.

555
00:44:38,875 --> 00:44:40,134
We have never been colonized.

556
00:44:42,048 --> 00:44:43,803
But we lost to extraterritoriality.

557
00:44:44,859 --> 00:44:46,384
Siamese needs to attend Western courts.

558
00:44:47,947 --> 00:44:49,160
I don't think that looked good.

559
00:44:50,395 --> 00:44:51,396
That's fine.

560
00:44:52,240 --> 00:44:54,008
People have freedom to express their ideas.

561
00:44:55,331 --> 00:44:57,450
They need to fulfill their duties to the fullest

562
00:44:58,008 --> 00:45:00,078
and organize the celebration to show our pride.

563
00:45:01,267 --> 00:45:03,640
We are all Siam's officials.

564
00:45:04,926 --> 00:45:06,264
We need to keep in mind that

565
00:45:06,659 --> 00:45:08,640
if we didn't have royal family members with great vision

566
00:45:08,707 --> 00:45:10,400
to grant scholarships to commoners to study,

567
00:45:11,336 --> 00:45:13,000
many soldiers around here

568
00:45:13,171 --> 00:45:14,920
would have been just a person with no future.

569
00:45:16,275 --> 00:45:17,276
Therefore,

570
00:45:17,854 --> 00:45:19,367
they shouldn't be ungrateful to the country.

571
00:45:43,667 --> 00:45:44,668
Did you have any idea what you just said?

572
00:45:44,782 --> 00:45:45,920
I said that truth.

573
00:45:46,275 --> 00:45:47,900
Did you know that if someone heard you,

574
00:45:47,920 --> 00:45:49,000
they could misinterpret of what you said?

575
00:45:49,272 --> 00:45:50,720
You could be in danger.

576
00:45:51,720 --> 00:45:54,840
Are you worried about me?

577
00:46:00,443 --> 00:46:01,800
You need to lead the army there

578
00:46:01,875 --> 00:46:03,680
and arrest all important royal family members.

579
00:46:03,756 --> 00:46:05,720
If they invade our area, shoot them all.

580
00:46:07,296 --> 00:46:09,560
Captain Phobthee have led the soldiers.

